task.summary: Files commented and packages updated : without warning and errors
Create User aggregate root entities : Admin, DepartmentHead, Teacher, Student
Faculty and Class aggregate roots : added static factory methods to roots, private constructors changed internal in entities;
Create UserRole entity and other roles (Admin, Student, ...) inherit from this. User.cs updated for this role;

feat: Implement role-based user creation with centralized role mapping
- Updated `CreateUserCommandHandler` to use `Role.FromName` for converting role names from the frontend into `Role` instances, leveraging the existing functionality in `Enumeration<TEnum>`. - Refactored `Role` to rely on the `Enumeration` base class for name-based lookup. - Enhanced error handling for invalid role names in `CreateUserCommandHandler`. - Added a new error definition `InvalidRoleName` in `DomainErrors.User`. - Improved `User.Create` method to handle role assignments seamlessly. - Cleaned up and optimized value object handling (e.g., `Email`, `FirstName`, `LastName`) in the command handler for better validation and error reporting.
This commit simplifies role mapping logic, ensures robust validation, and centralizes role-related operations for easier maintenance and extensibility.
New Permissions added and configurations updated accordingly
Decorated error fixed : new Domain event and handler created (UserCreatedDomainEvent) and using this domain event in User.cs
Migrations errors fixed : Sql Server -> PostgreSQL migrations
